description.narrative: Key actors are able to provide improved core child protection and GBV services for children at risk of or exposed to violence, exploitation and abuse in emergency and non-emergency,which contributes to Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). title.narrative: Key actors are able to provide improved core child protection and GBV services for children at risk of or exposed to violence, exploitation and abuse in emergency and non-emergency

description.narrative: UNICEF and partners supported 667,515 individuals with critical child protection services. This include family tracing and reunification (total caseload: 20,874 (F: 9,679 M:11,195), psychosocial support, mine risk education, gender-based violence prevention and response, and reintegration of children formerly associated with armed forces/groups. Key achievements include roll-out and training of case workers on case management SOPs and production of handbook; launch of CP Information Management System Plus and the practical guide for socio-economic reintegration of girls formerly associated with armed groups/forces and launch of PSS Facilitator's Manual and Trainer's Guide. CP and GBV continued its integration and mainstreaming in other sectors. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
